Strings area sequence of characters. 
Strings are not primitive data types, they are objects of a predefined class named 'String'.

String Operations;
      Get length - use length() method.
      join two strings - concat()
      compare two strings - equals()
      
Escape character is used to escape some of the characters present in a string, that is the \ (backslasH)
Strings are also immutable, once they are created they cannot be changed.
Strings can also be created using the new keyword since they are objects.
